The paper discusses tool support for the localization and repair of faults within knowledge bases, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses user studies to assess the practical value of query-based ontology debugging, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of different debugging approaches, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
